§ 390dd. Limitation on ownership Except as provided in section 390ii of this title, irrigation water may not be delivered to—(1) a qualified recipient for use in the irrigation of lands owned by such qualified recipient in excess of nine hundred and sixty acres of class I lands or the equivalent thereof; or
(2) a limited recipient for the use in the irrigation of lands owned by such limited recipient in excess of six hundred and forty acres of class I lands or the equivalent thereof;
whether situated in one or more districts. (Pub. L. 97–293, title II, § 204, Oct. 12, 1982, 96 Stat. 1265.)
